Seaborn is a statistical data visualization library in Python.
It is built on top of:
Matplotlib
Works very well with Pandas


Advantages of Seaborn:
Beautiful graphs
Less code
Built-in datasets
Easy statistical visualization


Seaborn already provides sample datasets for practice.
Example datasets:

tips
iris
titanic
flights


import seaborn as sns
data = sns.load_dataset("tips")
print(data.head())



import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
sns.scatterplot(x="total_bill", y="tip", data=data)
plt.show()



sns.scatterplot(x="total_bill", y="tip", hue="sex", data=data)
plt.show()


sns.histplot(data["total_bill"])
plt.show()


sns.countplot(x="day", data=data)
plt.show()


print(data["day"].unique())
